  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0da9\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dca \u0dad\u0dd4\u0db1\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dates are fixed for the three main breaks",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Education Mr. Susil Premjayantha announced in the Parliament the dates of the three main examinations held during the school term, the scholarship, advanced level and ordinary level examination.",
        "Accordingly, the A-level examination of the year 2022 is scheduled to be held from November 28 to December 23.",
        "There, the Minister further stated that the results of the 2021 General Certificate of Education A Level Examination will be released in the coming month of August.",
        "The minister also said that the fifth grade scholarship exam will be held on the 27th of November.",
        "The minister further mentioned that the general examination related to the year 2022 is planned to be held between April and May next year."
      ],
